==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Knotty
<hw>Knot"ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Knottier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Knottiest</adjf>.]</amorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Full of knots;
knotted; having many knots; <as>as, <ex>knotty</ex> timber; a
<ex>knotty</ex> rope.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hard; rugged; <as>as, a <ex>knotty</ex>
head</as>.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Rewe.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Difficult; intricate; perplexed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A <qex>knotty</qex> point to which we now proceed</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Knotweed</ent>⟦br⟧
